# Phase 3 Routine-Commerce Boundary

During Phase 3, ResQ Core work activates the documented data model and replaces helper stubs with real reads.

## Allowed Implementation

- Active taxonomy registration (`resq_audience`, `resq_concern`, `resq_ingredient`, `resq_product_role`, `resq_compliance_zone`)
- Active `resq_routine` CPT registration
- `register_post_meta()` and term meta with sanitize callbacks
- Real storefront helper implementations per `docs/12-PLUGIN-HELPER-CONTRACTS.md`
- Canonical resolver, compliance zone sync, cross-sell rules
- Transient cache for relationship lookups
- Native WP taxonomy panels (no custom metaboxes required)

## Prohibited in Phase 3

- No custom admin UI (option pages, product metaboxes, routine editor UI)
- No fixture data or WP-CLI seed scripts
- No REST endpoints
- No checkout/cart behavior changes
- No theme markup output from the plugin
- No bundle engine implementation
- Do not register superseded keys: `_resq_audience_ids`, `_resq_concern_ids`
- Do not store derived keys: `_resq_cbd_product`, `_resq_requires_compliance_notice`

